    • Field Detail

      • WHOLE

        public static final MusicalValue WHOLE
        Whole (1/1). Unlike other predefined MusicalValues this value does not have a fixed length in quarters but lasts a full bar whatever the Beat may be. This is used for a whole rest that lasts a full bar (instead of SEMIBREVE).

      • SEMIBREVE

      • isRelative

        public boolean isRelative()
        Determines if this value is relative. E.g. a SEMIBREVE (whole value, 1/1) is often consider to be equivalent to 4/4 as 4 times a QUARTER, what is actually wrong.
        Returns:
        true if fraction is 1 and the value is relative to the Beat, false otherwise.

      • isAbsolute

        public boolean isAbsolute()
        Returns:
        true if NOT relative (absolute), false otherwise.

      • isNormalized

        public boolean isNormalized()
        Returns:
        true if variation is MusicalValue.Variation.NONE, false otherwise.

      • toAbsoluteValue

        public MusicalValue toAbsoluteValue(Beat beat)
        Parameters:
        beat - the Beat used as base to make this MusicalValue absolute.
        Returns:
        the absolute MusicalValue according to the given Beat. Will return the current MusicalValue (this) if already absolute.

      • toNormalizedValue

        public MusicalValue toNormalizedValue()
        Returns:
        the normalized fraction of this MusicalValue so that variation is MusicalValue.Variation.NONE. Will return the current MusicalValue (this) if already normalized.
